Wladimir Klitschko Cancels Mormeck Fight Following Kidney Stone Operation

-- B y   J a m e s   C o n e
-- 
2011-12-05T12:01:24Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-05/wladimir-klitschko-cancels-mormeck-fight-following-kidney-stone-operation.html
Wladimir Klitschko’s world
heavyweight title fight against  France ’s Jean-Marc Mormeck has
been cancelled, the Ukrainian boxer said on his website.  The 35-year-old, who beat Britain’s David Haye in July, had
an operation at the weekend to remove a kidney stone. He was
scheduled to fight Mormeck, 39, in Dusseldorf,  Germany  on Dec.
10.   Klitschko holds the International Boxing Organization,
International Boxing Federation, World Boxing Organization and
World Boxing Association titles.  Klitschko’s has won 56 of his 59 fights, including 49
knockouts.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James Cone at 
 jcone@bloomberg.net  